ovements in Tailwind CSS v4, from the new engine to simplified configuration.\",\"tags\":[\"CSS\",\"Tailwind\",\"Web Design\"],\"author\":\"Lora\",\"body\":{\"raw\":\"\\n# Mastering Tailwind CSS v4\\n\\nTailwind CSS v4 brings a brand new engine written in Rust, offering incredible performance improvements and a simplified configuration experience.\\n\\n## What's New?\\n\\n### 1. The Oxide Engine\\nThe new engine is significantly faster, making build times almost instant.\\n\\n### 2. Zero Configuration\\nNo more `tailwind.config.js` by default. You can configure everything directly in your CSS.\\n\\n```css\\n@import \\\"tailwindcss\\\";\\n\\n@theme {\\n  --color-primary: #3b82f6;\\n  --font-sans: \\\"Inter\\\", sans-serif;\\n}\\n```\\n\\n### 3. CSS-first Configuration\\nVariables are now first-class citizens.\\n\\n## Migrating from v3\\n\\nMigration is straightforward for most projects. The main change is how you configure your theme and plugins.\\n\\n## Best Practices\\n\\n- Use semantic class names where possible\\n- Leverage the `@apply` directive sparingly\\n- embrace arbitrary values for one-off styles\\n\\nHappy styling!\\n\",\"code\":\"$19\"},\"_id\":\"blog/mastering-tailwind-v4.mdx\",\"_raw\":{\"sourceFilePath\":\"blog/mastering-tailwind-v4.mdx\",\"sourceFileName\":\"mastering-tailwind-v4.mdx\",\"sourceFileDir\":\"blog\",\"contentType\":\"mdx\",\"flattenedPath\":\"blog/mastering-tailwind-v4\"},\"type\":\"Post\",\"slug\":\"mastering-tailwind-v4\",\"slugAsParams\":\"mastering-tailwind-v4\",\"headings\":[{\"depth\":1,\"text\":\"Mastering Tailwind CSS v4\",\"url\":\"#mastering-tailwind-css-v4\",\"title\":\"Mastering Tailwind CSS v4\"},{\"depth\":2,\"text\":\"What's New?\",\"url\":\"#what's-new?\",\"title\":\"What's New?\"},{\"depth\":3,\"text\":\"1. The Oxide Engine\",\"url\":\"#1.-the-oxide-engine\",\"title\":\"1. The Oxide Engine\"},{\"depth\":3,\"text\":\"2. Zero Configuration\",\"url\":\"#2.-zero-configuration\",\"title\":\"2. Zero Configuration\"},{\"depth\"